headline: Podcast: U.S. Stocks Hit Record Highs on Shutdown’s Second Day
summary: A global surge in chip stocks led a rally that ended up with the Dow industrials, Nasdaq composite and S&P 500 at records. Plus: Tesla shares fell despite posting positive sales. And Starbucks raised its dividend.
